Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reset_min_pulse_width(25.10)                      reset_min_pulse_width(25.10)

Name
       reset_min_pulse_width  -  Resets  minimum pulse width constraint on the
       specified input ports of the top cell and the specified modules

Syntax
       reset_min_pulse_width

       [-help]

       <object_list>

       [-high]

       [-low]

       [-waveform_aware_type {absolute | source_width_ratio | all}]

       Resets minimum pulse width constraint on the specified input  ports  of
       the top cell and the specified modules.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -low   Resets  the  minimum  pulse width checks that are applied to low
              signal levels only.

       -high  Resets the minimum pulse width checks that are applied  to  high
              signal levels only.

       <object_list>
              Specifies  a list of pins or clock waveforms for which the mini-
              mum pulse width is to be reset. If a clock  waveform  is  speci-
              fied, all the pins driven by the clock are affected.

       -waveform_aware_type {absolute | source_width_ratio | all}
              Resets the regular and waveform-aware pulse width assertions.

Related Information
              * set_min_pulse_width

